            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-42-person387">
                  DAVID 
                  WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18190915-42-person387" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-42-person387" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-42-person387" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18190915-42-viclabel225" type="occupation">keep a public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190915-42-victim386 t18190915-42-viclabel225"></join> in <placeName id="t18190915-42-crimeloc226">Broad-street, St. Giles's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190915-42-crimeloc226" type="placeName" value="Broad-street, St. Giles's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190915-42-crimeloc226" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190915-42-off223 t18190915-42-crimeloc226"></join>; the prisoner had been quartered at my house for six months; he was under orders to march on the 28th of 
               <persName id="t18190915-42-person388">August. On</persName>
             the 27th, about ten o'clock at night, he came in to pack up his things, and brought another soldier with him; they were up stairs about an hour, then came down. While they were drinking some beer, my wife came down stairs, and said, in their hearing, that they had cut the bed open, and taken some feathers out, and that a pillow was missing. I asked the prisoner what he had got in his bundle? He said it was his foraging cap. He pulled the pillow from under his overalls.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-42-person389">
                  JOHN 
                  GOODWIN
               <interp inst="t18190915-42-person389" type="surname" value="GOODWIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-42-person389" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-42-person389" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am turncock of the New River. Williams called me in, and I saw the feathers in the prisoner's jacket; he unbuttoned his overalls and gave me the pillow - he said the other man had nothing to do with it. He appeared sober.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had drank near seven pots of porter, and was drunk.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18190915-42-verdict227" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18190915-42-verdict227" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 35.</p>
               <p>
